005package edu.wpi.first.units;
006
007/**
008 * Unit of power dimension.
009 *
010 * <p>This is the base type for units of power dimension. It is also used to specify the dimension
011 * for {@link Measure}: <code>Measure&lt;Power&gt;</code>.
012 *
013 * <p>Actual units (such as {@link Units#Watts} and {@link Units#Horsepower}) can be found in the
014 * {@link Units} class.
015 */
016public class Power extends Unit<Power> {
017  Power(double baseUnitEquivalent, String name, String symbol) {
018    super(Power.class, baseUnitEquivalent, name, symbol);
019  }
020
021  Power(
022      UnaryFunction toBaseConverter, UnaryFunction fromBaseConverter, String name, String symbol) {
023    super(Power.class, toBaseConverter, fromBaseConverter, name, symbol);
024  }
025}
